        <name>1.4.1.8 Cancelling Common Factors</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;h4 class="HELM_example"&gt;Example&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Simplify \(\dfrac{6(4-8x)(x-2)}{1-2x}\)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 class="HELM_solution"&gt;Solution&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The factor \(4-8x\) can be factorised to \(4(1-2x)\). Thus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\qquad \dfrac{6(4-8x)(x-2)}{1-2x} = \dfrac{(6)(4)(1-2x)(x-2)}{1-2x} = 24(x-2)\)&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
